8|Termination Rights & Kill Fees — Completed Jul 18, 2026. Key findings: (1) Kill fees as option consideration (termination for convenience) vs. liquidated damages (termination for breach under Restatement § 356); (2) Tiered cure periods added (5d payment / 15-30d performance / 0d non-curable); (3) Cumulative/pattern breach provision for death-by-a-thousand-cuts; (4) IP assignment conditioned on kill fee payment; (5) Kill fee enforceability acknowledgment with express difficulty-of-proof recital; (6) Transition assistance 30-day period; (7) Kill fee added to survival clause. Updated Clause Genome §18 (3 lines → 80+ lines), MSA §2.6 (enforceability acknowledgment + IP condition), MSA §9 (tiered cure, pattern breach, transition, insolvency distinction, survival update). Version: Genome 1.9.0→1.10.0, MSA 1.4→1.5.